Key Responsibilities:

Report to the team head, perform daily settlement operation (daily processing, corporate actions, physical certificates, stock and cash management, trade and stock reconciliation, IPO and placing, etc.) and monitor the operational activities in respect to the requirements of SFC, IRD, HKEx etc.
Handle daily booking and ensure all trading processing are completed correctly and properly; Liaise and resolve settlement issues with clients and counterparties;
Prepare the settlement payments, receipts and reports;
Handle Market Rehearsal and system UAT when necessary;
Handle data input and new account opening with settlement system;
Assist in account opening, KYC documents for our asset management team;
Handle other ad hoc duties.

Requirements:

Degree holder in any discipline;
Around 1-3 years relevant experience;
Knowledge of CCASS, (iAsia Online) iBoss systems is preferred;
Good PC knowledge including Excel and MS Word;
Good command of written and spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Self-motivated, detail oriented, reliable with good communication skills.
We offer Competitive Remuneration and Benefits package including Double Pay, Performance Bonus, Group Medical & Dental and Career Prospects to the right candidates.


Interested parties please send your full resume with expected salary to us by clicking "Apply Now".

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

For details, please visit our official website: http://www.jqshk.com/index_hk.html

Global Banking & Markets - Global Markets Operations


Hang Seng's Global Markets Operations is a team of experienced banking operations professionals who strive for delivering time-to-market, efficient and world-class processing services to customers, corporations, financial institutions and internal units. We are responsible for driving every part of the trade lifecycle post execution. We manage settlement activity, risk and control, while ensuring the delivery of regulatory compliance and seamless operational client services.



We are currently seeking a high caliber professional to join our department as Global Markets Operations Manager.

 Principal responsibilities

Handle post-trade processing of Fixed Income products and perform life cycle management / settlement via BO systems;
Oversee daily operations to ensure compliance with internal and related regulatory requirements;
Provide support on project / systems implementation, workflow design, and process re-engineering in supporting Global Markets Operations;
Work closely with various stakeholders including business users, IT departments, legal and compliance to ensure effective operations

Requirements

University degree in a related discipline OR other relevant qualifications;
Minimum of five years' banking experience in products settlement preferably in GM products;
Attentiveness to details and self-motivated with the ability to work independently and under pressure;
Resilient, capable to work responsibly in a dynamic environment;
Proficiency in both English and Chinese, fluency in Putonghua an advantage;
Great sense of ownership and servicing mindset to ensure efficient and effective customer service processes

If you would like to explore other opportunities at Hang Seng Hong Kong, please visit www.hangseng.com/careers/ for details.

The health and safety of our employees and candidates is very important to us. Due to the current situation related to the Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV), we’re leveraging our digital capabilities to ensure we can continue to recruit top talent at the HSBC Group.  As your application progresses, you may be asked to use one of our digital tools to help you through your recruitment journey.  If so, one of our Resourcing colleagues will explain how our video-interviewing technology will be used throughout the recruitment process and will be on hand to answer any questions you might have.
All information provided by applicants will be used only for recruitment purposes and will be used strictly in accordance with the Bank's personal data policies, a copy of which may be obtained by the applicant upon request. Unless otherwise instructed in writing by the applicant concerned, applicants may be considered for other suitable positions within the Bank and its related companies. The personal data of unsuccessful job applicants may be retained for a maximum of two years from the date when the job application is rejected and such data may be retained for a longer period if there is a subsisting reason that obliges the Bank to do so, after which the personal data will be destroyed.

Requirements:

Perform the daily operations of settlements;
Responsible for futures/options and bonds settlement;
Corporate action for equities and bonds market;
Estimate funding requirement for equities, derivatives and bonds market;
Client & exchange / broker trade and position reconciliation;
Client money segregation;
Provides quality support to both internal and external clients for ad hoc and regular queries;
Project participation and implementation for new business/system enhancement;
Ensure appropriate controls are in place to comply with internal policy.

Qualifications:

Minimum 3 years of experience in Operations or Settlement;
Degree in Business, Finance, Mathematics, Risk Management, Statistics or a related discipline;
Attain professional qualification(s) in Investment Banking, Risk Management or other  relevant subject is preferred;
Supervisory experience is advantageous.

Duties and Responsibilities

Perform trade matching & arrange trade settlement for funds & discretionary accounts;
Assist in the trade matching system implementation (Omgeo CTM/ In house system);
Assist in delay trade settlement aging report & follow up with trade settlement;
Perform holding / cash reconciliations;
Perform daily cash forecast;
Liaise with internal departments for fee analysis & arrange payment;
Assist in account opening/ closure with counterparties for funds launch/termination;
Provide secretarial support to the team;
Perform ad hoc tasks in professional & timely manner;
Require to work shift and holiday support.
Assist in system development relating to trade matching and settlement.
Requirements
Bachelor degree holder in Accounting, Finance or related disciplines;
0-2 yearsof relevant working experience;
Professional education preferred (CFA or CPA);
Knowledge of Bloomberg and Reuters;
Proficiency in VBA, Python preferred.
Languages Skills: Fluent in English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
A strong team player;
Prioritization and multi-tasking skills;
Self-motivatedand able to work independently;
Immediately available will be an advantage;
Fresh graduates are welcome.
Compensation and Benefits  

E Fund HK is a fast growing company with strong financial resources and parent company support. We offer competitive compensations and career growth opportunities. We also offer attractive benefit programsand continued education support.

