Supervise day-to-day settlement and operational support in the following areas: FX/ MM, Repo, NDF, OTC Option, ARR IRS, ARR Bonds etc. Liaise with counterparties and Front Office if there is trade booking discrepancy, confirmation mismatched, and settlement issues relating to Treasury transactions. Perform Collateral Management tasks, collaterals transfer, calculation of collateral interests, and arrangement settlement with CSA counterparties (Variation Margin & Initial Margin). Participate in system enhancement project, manage and resolve problems during different stages from project initiation to its implementation. Produce documentation on operating procedures and operating guideline Optimize workflow of the supervised business routine, so as to enhance operating efficiency and cost-effectiveness

Requirements:

Degree holder;
Minimum 8 years of working experience in the settlement department;
Solid experience of the operations and settlement of FX/MM, Repo, OTC Option, ARR IRS, ARR Bonds etc;
Familiar with settlement systems such as SWIFT, eMBT/eCMT, CMU and Euclid;
Strong commitment, drive, willing to learn, and able to meet tight deadlines;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese.

Candidate with more experience will be considered as Senior Settlement Manager.

