“We” are the largest Belgian bank with Asian activities in Singapore, Shanghai and Hong Kong.  Each and every day our team in Asia strives to become the Preferred European Banking Partner of our domestic and European customers. To do so, we combine high professional standards and a pleasant working environment and we put our customers in the center point in everything we do. Also our internal customers!

We are looking for an enthusiastic and self-motivating talent to join our team as the Junior Officer of Remittance and Settlement Team. You can have the exposure in full remittance and settlement process in the international banking.

 About the job

As the Junior Officer of Remittance and Settlement team, you process inward and outward remittance;
You handle and respond to inquiries / requests from inter-department, customers, on transaction processing and related matters;
You perform customer FX transactions, as well as participating in AML screening on incoming & outgoing swift payments;
You manage the daily operations through SWIFT/ RTGS system;
You manage the general administrative duties of your team and assist in ad hoc duties as assigned by superiors.

About you

To join the KBC team, you need to be a good team player, with ability to communicate clearly and concisely. You are with good command of spoken and written English, Chinese & Mandarin, as well as great self-motivation and self-starting ability. You need to be familiar AML screening and SWIFT/ RTGS system. You should also attain tertiary qualification and have minimum 3 years’ relevant experience. Finally, need to be eager to learn and continuously develop yourself to remain future proof in a swiftly changing environment. If you are having less experience, we may also considered you as Senior Clerk.

We offer an attractive remuneration package in line with your relevant experience and the importance of the position.  

If you feel like this position is a fit with your skill-set and expectations, please apply with a cover letter and CV (indicating your salary expectation) by email via "Apply Now". For any questions with regards to the position you can give us a call on  (852) 2879 3363.


